r bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usorchacohen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SorchaCohen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/13/02 7:09:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://rodden.net/webgfx/sashield60.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: THE WAR OF THE GODS IS AT HAND!!</span><hr size=1> Thanks Dorn. I'm not a religious scholar, I just have a passing facination and horror with it. <br><br>&lt;hijack&gt;<br>From what I can tell, the origins of most of the popular religions (by which I encompass all forms of christianity, islam, judaism and similar non-christian old testament stuff, hinduism, buddhism, celtic 'paganism' (for want of a better word) etc) can be traced to old religions of zoroastrianism, mithranism and on again to their roots. Each inherited a set of values then adapted it to local conditions, fashion and the whim of the rulers of the time.<br><br>Dang, says Henry. I don't like the churchmen telling me I'm stuck with this witch of a wife. I know, I'll make a few changes to what God said we could do, call it the new official religion, and hook up with someone younger and cuter! It's good to be the king!<br><br>Human brains all tend to operate in similar ways so I see it as quite reasonable that diverse cultures would develop similar explanations for way of things. It's amusing to look at some of the dictated-by-deity religious laws and compare them to 'good practices'. For example, islam's separation of one hand for eating, the other for wiping. In a culture that doesn't understand germ theory (and the importance of washing/disinfecting your hands) that's a good practice! Similarly the food prep rules strong in both islam and judaism are an excellent way of avoiding upset stomachs in a pre-germ-theory culture.<br><br>Facinating stuff, watching the human mind at work!<br>&lt;/hijack&gt; <p>Sorcha Cohen<br>Druid of the 11th Death Touch<br><a href="http://southernarmada.virtualave.net/">Southern Armada</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usespetoxri.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sespetoxri</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/21/02 10:23:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: THE WAR OF THE GODS IS AT HAND!!</span><hr size=1> Actually I would argue the human condition itself is the connecting key between most religions.  Most people want the same basic things in life, and most realize they cannot have them- therefore they create a utopian existance for after their death, or another chance at life again through a reincarnation-esque theology.  I would hasten to point out the time frame we're dealing with when we ask which religion begat the following...  after all, it's difficult to suggest celtic paganism spawned christianity, as the sheer volume of contact necessary to make this happen was nonexistant at the time.  There was, of course, enough of a cultural mix to make your arguement valid, but I think it's easier to simply say it's along the lines of convergent theology.  Different peoples and places developed religions along similar lines due to the wants and needs of the people, rather than a far more simplistic explanation of 'borrowing' what they like from one religion to create their own.<br><br>Just my 2cp, of course, we weren't really there during the great Catholocism Planning Session. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><p align="center"><img border="0" src="http://www.yannieshaven.5u.com/images/Ses54.jpg"></p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm18.showNextMessage?topicID=41.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/addReply1.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm18.emailToFriend?topicID=41.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm18.threadControl?topicID=41.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/deleteThreadFire.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm18.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=41.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm18.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=41.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="prexus95980general">General<option value=